HEADWORD: Fiddlewood
<hw>Fid"dle*wood`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr.
F. bois-<ets>fid⟦egrave⟧le</ets>, lit., faithful wood; -- so called from
its durability.]</ety> <def>The wood of several West Indian trees,
mostly of the genus <gen>Citharexylum</gen>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

